AGI - "We must disarm the words, disarm the minds and disarm the Earth. There is a great need for reflection, pacacity, sense of complexity." This is what Pope Francis wrote in a letter of 14 March addressed to the editor of Corriere, Luciano Fontana>, and published on the website of the newspaper.
"While the war does nothing but devastate communities and the environment, without offering solutions to conflicts," says " diplomacy and international organizations need new life and credibility. Religions can also draw on the spirituality of peoples to rekindle the desire for brotherhood and justice, the hope of peace. All this calls for commitment, work, silence, words," continued the pontiff in the missive, written in response to a greeting message from Fontana for his health."
Francesco, from the hospital Gemelli> where he has been hospitalized for over a month, has launched an exhortation to the manager of the Corriere and to "all who dedicate work and intelligence to inform, through tools of communication that now unite our world in real time: feel all the importance of words. They are never only words: they are made that build human environments. They can connect or divide, serve the truth or serve it." &nbsp;

